result:
Tested 20+ properties on collections.abc - all passed ✅

The module appears to be robust. I tested:
- Set operations (intersection, union, difference, XOR) and their mathematical properties
- MutableSet in-place operations including edge cases with self-operations
- Sequence operations including index/count with identity vs equality checks
- MutableSequence reverse idempotence and pop/append inverse operations
- MutableMapping update, setdefault, and popitem edge cases
- Hash computation consistency and boundary conditions
- Comparison operations transitivity and reflexivity

No genuine bugs were found. The implementations correctly handle edge cases like NaN comparisons, empty collections, and self-references.
